Docs.summary:
Represents a sorted set that enables changes with little or no memory allocations, and efficiently manipulates or builds immutable sorted sets.
**NuGet package**: System.Collections.Immutable (about immutable collections and how to install)

remarks.format: ## Remarks Although <xref:System.Collections.Immutable.ImmutableSortedSet%601.Union%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> and other methods already provide fast bulk change operations on a collection, the <xref:System.Collections.Immutable.ImmutableSortedSet%601.Builder> class enables multiple combinations of changes to be made to a set with equal or greater efficiency, depending on the operation.
